[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Ad [Addendum] 54. Witt Library. P.B.II. Kermis with Stage (like Perth but horizontal): a) with left bottom corner empty: 1) Duc de Croÿ-Dülmen Coll. (formerly Demotte, Paris - Brussels Exh. 1935, N° 148 (?); 2) Biljoen Sale, Muller Amsterdam, 28 May 1918, N° 128, Panel 112 x 166 cm, signed and dated 1624; 3) J. Leger, London 1930, 80 x 42 in.; [blad 1, verso] b) with wrestlers added in left bottom corner. Fitzwilliam Museum Cambridge, signed and dated P. BREVGHEL 1632; c) like b) but three more boys added at left bottom. Notes by Goodison with these reproduction: A) Clarembaux, on canvas, 120 x 160 cm, signed P.BRVEGEL 1550; B) Demotte - Biljoen; C) Graz, signed P. 114 x 168 cm; D) Fiévez Sale, Brussels, May 17-18, 1923, 114 x 165 cm; E) Private Coll. Genoa, Quite different; [blad 2, recto] Ad 54. Witt Library. P.B.II. Kermesse with stage continued: D) Fragment, cut out from upper half: as 'Le Foir du marché' in Schaubroek Sale, Giroux, Brussels, 3-5 May 1927, N° 320, Bois 62 x 90 cm, 'agrandi dans le ciel sur une hauteur de 5 cm.' Yes!
